SIMPLE: easily
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Easily
<hw>Eas"i*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Easy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>With ease; without difficulty or
much effort; <as>as, this task may be <ex>easily</ex> performed; that
event might have been <ex>easily</ex> foreseen.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without pain, anxiety, or disturbance; <as>as, to
pass life well and <ex>easily</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Temple.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Readily; without reluctance; willingly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not soon provoked, she <qex>easily</qex> forgives.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 467 --></p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Smoothly; quietly; gently; gracefully; without
tumult or discord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Without shaking or jolting; commodiously; <as>as, a
carriage moves <ex>easily</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Easiness</ent>⟦br⟧
